South African Taxi Accident Kills 30, Injures Seven, SAPA Says

-- B y   M i k e   C o h e n
-- 
2011-12-10T08:38:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-10/south-african-taxi-accident-kills-30-injures-seven-sapa-says.html
A collision between an overloaded
taxi and a truck in central  South Africa  claimed the lives of 30
people, 10 of them children, the South Africa Press Association
reported, citing police spokesman Mmako Mophiring.  The minibus taxi, carrying 35 people on a freeway near the
town of Harrismith in Free State Province when the crash
happened, was certified to transport only 23, Mophiring said,
according to the Johannesburg-based news agency.  Seven people were also hospitalized, SAPA said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mike Cohen in  Cape Town  at 
 mcohen21@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at   barden@bloomberg.net  